Look!

1066
01:34:40,220 --> 01:34:42,575
- The Zeppelin! - We've found Grandpa.

1067
01:34:42,660 --> 01:34:44,537
Not yet we haven't.

1068
01:35:00,380 --> 01:35:02,610
What's happening?

1069
01:35:02,700 --> 01:35:05,419
- Remarkable! - Your Excellency...

1070
01:35:05,500 --> 01:35:07,730
- We are being attacked. - Attacked?

1071
01:35:07,820 --> 01:35:09,173
Attack! Attack!

1072
01:35:09,380 --> 01:35:12,133
That was that terrible Bomburst!

1073
01:35:12,220 --> 01:35:14,529
It certainly was.

1074
01:35:14,620 --> 01:35:16,690
- Where are they going? - It's a car!

1075
01:35:16,780 --> 01:35:18,179
Where did they go?

1076
01:35:20,300 --> 01:35:22,894
How floaty in the heavenly abode, fully peoplebodies.

1077
01:35:26,060 --> 01:35:26,412
Fire!

1078
01:35:26,500 --> 01:35:30,209
What's the matter with you? You want to destroy my beautiful car?

1079
01:35:30,820 --> 01:35:32,651
They're firing at us.

1080
01:35:32,740 --> 01:35:36,050
There are children up there.

1081
01:35:36,140 --> 01:35:38,096
We'd better get away from here.

1082
01:35:39,980 --> 01:35:43,211
Hang on, everybody. We're coming in to land.

1083
01:35:43,300 --> 01:35:46,929
Your Excellency, it's landing in the village.

1084
01:35:47,020 --> 01:35:49,329
Call out the guards!

1085
01:35:58,820 --> 01:36:00,731
And call out the child catcher!

1086
01:36:06,860 --> 01:36:08,054
Charge!

1087
01:36:13,260 --> 01:36:14,454
Charge!

1088
01:36:18,660 --> 01:36:20,093
Let me in.

1089
01:36:31,420 --> 01:36:33,809
We made it!

1090
01:36:36,060 --> 01:36:38,051
- Isn't Chitty wonderful? - You're clever, Daddy.

1091
01:36:38,140 --> 01:36:40,529
Yes, he certainly is.

1092
01:36:40,620 --> 01:36:42,850
You all stay here. I'm going to the castle.

1093
01:36:42,940 --> 01:36:45,374
- We want to come too. - To help you find Grandpa.

1094
01:36:45,460 --> 01:36:48,133
Don't you think we ought to stay together?

1095
01:36:48,220 --> 01:36:51,292
- Maybe you're right. - Come on, children.

1096
01:36:54,020 --> 01:36:56,295
- I wonder where we are. - I don't know.

1097
01:36:56,900 --> 01:36:58,492
Come on.

1098
01:37:02,580 --> 01:37:05,538
Pardon me, sir. The castle?

1099
01:37:05,620 --> 01:37:08,453
- Le chateau? - Der Schloss?

1100
01:37:10,020 --> 01:37:12,978
What's the matter with him?

1101
01:37:13,060 --> 01:37:15,051
Come on.

1102
01:37:44,420 --> 01:37:47,298
What are they staring at?

1103
01:37:47,380 --> 01:37:49,575
I don't know.

1104
01:37:52,220 --> 01:37:54,529
It seems to be the children.

1105
01:37:54,620 --> 01:37:57,612
Haven't they seen children before?

1106
01:37:59,140 --> 01:38:01,335
Haven't you noticed?

1107
01:38:01,420 --> 01:38:03,695
There aren't any children.

1108
01:38:04,900 --> 01:38:06,652
Not one.

1109
01:38:12,100 --> 01:38:14,136
What's going on?

1110
01:38:16,660 --> 01:38:19,379
Hey, you, what's happening?

1111
01:38:19,740 --> 01:38:21,332
Soldiers! Soldiers!

1112
01:38:29,780 --> 01:38:31,771
Hey, you there!

1113
01:38:31,860 --> 01:38:35,011
- Get the children in here. - Can you tell me what's happening?

1114
01:38:35,100 --> 01:38:37,295
Quickly, before the soldiers get here.

1115
01:38:37,380 --> 01:38:42,010
Come, Fraulein. Get inside, quickly.

1116
01:38:43,420 --> 01:38:48,096
We must hide the children. The soldiers will take them away.

1117
01:38:48,180 --> 01:38:49,818
But why?

1118
01:38:49,900 --> 01:38:52,619
Nobody's allowed to have children in Vulgaria.

1119
01:38:52,700 --> 01:38:57,615
- But what about all these toys? - The baroness hates children.

1120
01:38:57,700 --> 01:39:00,931
Quickly, down there. And don't make a sound.

1121
01:39:19,740 --> 01:39:23,892
I want every house in this square to be searched from top to bottom.

1122
01:39:23,980 --> 01:39:26,130
First section, step out there and search.

1123
01:39:26,220 --> 01:39:30,498
Second section, over there. Section three, over there.

1124
01:39:31,900 --> 01:39:33,970
Search everywhere!

1125
01:39:37,020 --> 01:39:38,533
Giddap!

1126
01:39:43,860 --> 01:39:48,172
There are children here somewhere.

1127
01:39:48,260 --> 01:39:51,332
I can smell them.

1128
01:39:52,020 --> 01:39:54,136
Aaah-ha!

1129
01:39:55,140 --> 01:39:56,778
Captain!

1130
01:39:56,860 --> 01:39:59,852
I think we've got them.

1131
01:39:59,940 --> 01:40:03,569
- Lieutenant! - Break down this door.

1132
01:40:04,420 --> 01:40:06,217
Get this door open.

1133
01:40:06,300 --> 01:40:07,972
All right. I'm coming.

1134
01:40:08,060 --> 01:40:10,733
Bang the door down! Quickly!

1135
01:40:11,700 --> 01:40:14,009
You've no right to come in here!

1136
01:40:14,100 --> 01:40:16,614
- Search the place! - Search! Search!

1137
01:40:18,700 --> 01:40:20,656
A- ha!

1138
01:40:21,060 --> 01:40:23,699
They are here somewhere.

1139
01:40:23,780 --> 01:40:26,499
I can feel it in my bones.

1140
01:40:26,580 --> 01:40:29,458
There are children here.

1141
01:40:29,540 --> 01:40:33,852
Children in a toy shop. Such a notion. I mean...

1142
01:40:33,940 --> 01:40:37,376
What are you doing? That's for the baron's birthday.

1143
01:40:37,460 --> 01:40:40,816
Let me tell you, toymaker.

1144
01:40:40,900 --> 01:40:45,257
This nose of mine has never failed me.

1145
01:40:45,340 --> 01:40:50,368
And if there are children here, my friend,

1146
01:40:50,460 --> 01:40:53,816
you will die.

1147
01:40:57,780 --> 01:40:59,771
A- ha!

1148
01:41:02,580 --> 01:41:06,175
Quick, open it up. Get down there and search the cellar.

1149
01:41:09,260 --> 01:41:12,297
The baroness will have your teeth for a necklace

1150
01:41:12,380 --> 01:41:15,338
and your eyeballs for earrings.

1151
01:41:15,420 --> 01:41:20,858
- Nobody down here. - Fool. Idiot. Out of my way.

1152
01:41:20,940 --> 01:41:24,979
You have to know where to look.

1153
01:41:25,060 --> 01:41:29,292
Like cockroaches they get under the floors,

1154
01:41:29,380 --> 01:41:31,814
in the cracks in the walls,

1155
01:41:31,900 --> 01:41:34,698
in the woodwork.

1156
01:42:11,300 --> 01:42:15,213
I don't trust a man who makes toys

1157
01:42:15,300 --> 01:42:20,135
in a land where children are forbidden.

1158
01:42:20,220 --> 01:42:23,417
Every toy I make is exclusively for His Excellency the Baron.

1159
01:42:23,500 --> 01:42:27,379
Captain, ze flying car. We've captured ze flying car.

1160
01:42:27,460 --> 01:42:29,132
Fall in! Fall in!

1161
01:42:47,740 --> 01:42:49,810
Take zis car to the castle.

1162
01:42:53,100 --> 01:42:57,139
- They can't take Chitty. - Daddy, do something.

1163
01:42:57,220 --> 01:43:00,257
- What are you going to do? - I'm not just gonna stand here.

1164
01:43:00,340 --> 01:43:04,379
Are you mad? Are you going to take on the whole army single-handed?

1165
01:43:11,980 --> 01:43:14,448
What kind of a country is this?

1166
01:43:14,540 --> 01:43:16,371
No children.

1167
01:43:16,460 --> 01:43:18,928
Everybody terrified out of their lives.

1168
01:43:19,020 --> 01:43:21,409
My friend, take some good advice.

1169
01:43:21,500 --> 01:43:25,334
Take your children and your good lady and get out of Vulgaria.

1170
01:43:25,420 --> 01:43:29,732
And leave Grandpa up in the castle? We need to get him out.

1171
01:43:29,820 --> 01:43:32,812
- Just tell me how to get there. - I'm only a toymaker.

1172
01:43:32,900 --> 01:43:36,973
If I don't finish this for the baron's birthday, I shall be a dead toymaker.

1173
01:43:37,060 --> 01:43:40,370
I'll go myself. Truly, you stay here with the children.

1174
01:43:40,460 --> 01:43:42,451
All right, all right.

1175
01:43:45,860 --> 01:43:49,535
You don't know what you're letting yourself in for.

1176
01:43:50,900 --> 01:43:54,609
- Here's one for you, one for you. - Thank you, toymaker.

1177
01:43:54,700 --> 01:43:56,895
Keep them out of sight, please.

1178
01:43:56,980 --> 01:43:59,096
You be good and do what Truly tells you.

1179
01:43:59,180 --> 01:44:00,852
- We will. - Yes, Daddy.

1180
01:44:01,260 --> 01:44:03,979
Are you coming?

1181
01:44:16,140 --> 01:44:17,334
Come.

1182
01:44:23,380 --> 01:44:25,735
Quickly!

1183
01:44:29,380 --> 01:44:31,769
There isn't a scrap of food in the place.

1184
01:44:31,860 --> 01:44:36,172
- I'm so hungry, my tummy hurts. - Mine is making funny noises.

1185
01:44:36,260 --> 01:44:38,615
I simply must find something for you.

1186
01:44:38,700 --> 01:44:41,373
Promise not to move from here until I come back.

1187
01:44:41,460 --> 01:44:43,530
- We promise, don't we? - Yes.

1188
01:44:43,620 --> 01:44:46,373
Remember, you stay right here.

1189
01:44:52,420 --> 01:44:56,254
To get in that way, you have to be a mouse, or a magician.

1190
01:45:02,340 --> 01:45:05,457
We should go down now before a sentry sees us.

1191
01:45:05,540 --> 01:45:07,735
Come. Come.

1192
01:45:11,060 --> 01:45:13,051
The flying car.

1193
01:45:14,140 --> 01:45:17,212
At last it's mine.

1194
01:45:17,300 --> 01:45:20,292
Send for the inventor.

1195
01:45:20,820 --> 01:45:22,811
Now, then, fly.

1196
01:45:22,900 --> 01:45:24,652
- Yes, fly. - Fly.

1197
01:45:24,740 --> 01:45:26,810
- Come on. Fly. - Fly, fly, fly.

1198
01:45:27,820 --> 01:45:29,811
I command you to fly!

1199
01:45:31,020 --> 01:45:31,736
Watch it.

1200
01:45:31,820 --> 01:45:34,812
- Over here. - Hello! What's this doing here?

1201
01:45:34,900 --> 01:45:38,415
You are the inventor. Make this car fly.

1202
01:45:38,500 --> 01:45:41,810
Make it fly. Go on. Get in.

1203
01:45:44,180 --> 01:45:47,138
Stand back, everyone. We are going to fly.

1204
01:45:47,220 --> 01:45:50,257
Yoo-hoo, Bombie, wait for me!

1205
01:45:50,340 --> 01:45:53,616
Every time I want to have a little fun, she turns up.

1206
01:45:56,380 --> 01:45:59,292
My darling, we are going for a fly.

1207
01:45:59,380 --> 01:46:03,373
How exciting. Fly. How thrilling.

1208
01:46:03,460 --> 01:46:06,497
- Hurry up. - I am doing my best, sir.

1209
01:46:06,580 --> 01:46:09,492
Just a minute. Here's one we haven't tried.

1210
01:46:09,580 --> 01:46:12,140
- Here we go, my beloved. - Hold on!

1211
01:46:13,780 --> 01:46:16,499
Isn't it exciting, my dear?

1212
01:46:21,860 --> 01:46:24,693
You are a genius. Bring my guns.

1213
01:46:24,780 --> 01:46:27,578
Don't worry, little pigeon. I'll get you down.

1214
01:46:27,660 --> 01:46:31,096
I've been waiting for this for 20 years.

1215
01:46:31,740 --> 01:46:35,096
Are you still there, my love? Don't move.

1216
01:46:43,700 --> 01:46:46,453
There she is, Your Excellency.

1217
01:46:46,540 --> 01:46:48,690
My diamonds!

1218
01:46:48,780 --> 01:46:51,010
Are you all right, my dear?

1219
01:46:51,660 --> 01:46:54,174
I'm all right, my dumpling.

1220
01:46:54,780 --> 01:46:58,011
Good. Never mind. I'll get her the next time.

1221
01:47:13,460 --> 01:47:18,773
Here we are, children. Come and get your lollipops.

1222
01:47:20,620 --> 01:47:22,258
Lollipops.

1223
01:47:22,340 --> 01:47:25,059
Come along, my little ones.

1224
01:47:25,140 --> 01:47:27,131
Lollipops.

1225
01:47:30,340 --> 01:47:34,538
Ice cream. Chocolate. All free today.

1226
01:47:34,620 --> 01:47:36,690
Listen.

1227
01:47:38,860 --> 01:47:40,259
What's that?

1228
01:47:44,180 --> 01:47:47,934
Children, where are you?

1229
01:47:49,140 --> 01:47:52,610
I know you're here somewhere.

1230
01:47:54,300 --> 01:47:58,851
I've lots of lovely goodies for you.

1231
01:47:58,940 --> 01:48:01,534
Jeremy, you mustn't.

1232
01:48:04,940 --> 01:48:06,931
Lollipops.

1233
01:48:07,740 --> 01:48:11,972
And all free today.

1234
01:48:12,060 --> 01:48:13,732
Cherry pies,

1235
01:48:13,820 --> 01:48:15,856
cream puffs,

1236
01:48:15,940 --> 01:48:17,578
ice cream,

1237
01:48:17,660 --> 01:48:19,457
treacle tarts.

1238
01:48:19,540 --> 01:48:22,338
- Treacle tarts. - And ice creams.

1239
01:48:22,420 --> 01:48:24,012
And all free.

1240
01:48:24,100 --> 01:48:27,888
Come along, kiddiwinkies.

1241
01:48:28,380 --> 01:48:31,770
- Come on. - Truly said we mustn't.

1242
01:48:31,860 --> 01:48:34,897
We'll get Truly some as well.

1243
01:48:38,220 --> 01:48:40,176
Mr Man...

1244
01:48:40,820 --> 01:48:43,653
Children, come back.

1245
01:48:46,180 --> 01:48:48,171
Children, come back here.

1246
01:48:51,220 --> 01:48:53,176
Come along, my little dears,

1247
01:48:53,260 --> 01:48:55,057
my little mice.

1248
01:48:55,140 --> 01:48:57,131
Come to me.

1249
01:48:57,940 --> 01:49:00,500
What will it be? Ice cream?

1250
01:49:00,580 --> 01:49:04,698
Strawberry, chocolate, vanilla. It's all inside.

1251
01:49:04,780 --> 01:49:06,850
Come along, my little dears.

1252
01:49:06,940 --> 01:49:09,295
Not a penny to pay.

1253
01:49:09,380 --> 01:49:12,133
Go inside, my little dears.

1254
01:49:31,460 --> 01:49:33,132
Children!

1255
01:49:37,380 --> 01:49:39,018
Truly.

1256
01:49:39,100 --> 01:49:40,579
Help! Help!

1257
01:49:40,660 --> 01:49:44,050
- What's happened? - He took the children.

1258
01:49:48,780 --> 01:49:51,658
Your Excellency.

1259
01:49:51,740 --> 01:49:54,334
- Let us out. - Silence.

1260
01:50:04,860 --> 01:50:07,772
Children, Your Highness.

1261
01:50:07,860 --> 01:50:12,217
Foreign children. Unique specimens.

1262
01:50:12,300 --> 01:50:14,655
You're sure they can't get out?

1263
01:50:14,740 --> 01:50:16,731
No, Your Highness.

1264
01:50:17,780 --> 01:50:22,729
Perhaps Your Highness would care to examine them.

1265
01:50:22,820 --> 01:50:28,099
Nasty little creatures. Very, very treacherous. Foreign.

1266
01:50:30,140 --> 01:50:35,931
- Wait till our daddy hears about this. - He'll blow up the whole castle.

1267
01:50:36,020 --> 01:50:39,012
Take them away to the tower.

1268
01:50:40,060 --> 01:50:42,255
You're a nasty, horrid, mean old lady.

1269
01:50:42,340 --> 01:50:45,298
And very ugly.

1270
01:50:45,380 --> 01:50:47,769
Oh, she's going.

1271
01:51:13,620 --> 01:51:18,614
200 feet above us through that solid rock is the castle of Baron Bomburst.

1272
01:51:48,780 --> 01:51:50,816
These are our children.

1273
01:51:50,900 --> 01:51:55,769
For five years, we have hidden them here.

1274
01:51:55,860 --> 01:52:01,457
